caption: Best coffee bar in existence! Customer service is great and they offer a variety of drinks and vegan pastries. The owner takes pride in his business and it shows! They just started offering breakfast sandwiches and there is something In there for everyone from vegetarian, vegan, or if you simply aren’t either. Chase and the other lady at the counter always take the time to find out how your day is going and if you need any adjustment to your drink they will do it with a smile on their face! Oh and they have a Mediterranean restaurant on 167 street that’s just as good!  Please do visit this small business!
The best coffee that I ever had for the last year ❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️
HORRIBLE EXPERIENCE!!!!!!!!  Today I went this coffee place and I almost started "crying" because the barista was so rude without no reason. I only asked for one bagel. I will never go back.
Great tea and bagels  in Washington heights. I highly recommend

I really want to like this place, but every time I go in I have a terrible experience. Today I went in and ordered two caramel macchiatos to go. The barista immediately said in a rather rude tone “we make them the traditional way”. Once I received the macchiatos, I asked for lids. The barista scoffed and said “no”, and gave me a look like I was asking for his social security number. I requested larger cups with lids and he placed one cup on the counter with no lid. I grabbed my own lid from the top of the espresso machine,  even though that’s definitely not a covid 19 safe behavior. Then had to combine the macchiatos into one cup, therefore leaving with one drink instead of two, so I didn’t get any coffee. I think I offended him by not appreciating his foam art even though I did give him a 50% tip. This place is too pretentious for the neighborhood.
I've never been to this place before, even though it's near my work. It surprised me. Nice atmosphere, good coffee and I want to mention the pastries. Everyone is welcome!
Yeah , good coffee!
Beautiful atmosphere, great coffee by Irving Farm and tasty pastries and goodies. Love it!
Cute space, good coffee, nice barista. Wonderful.
Great shop. They've survived the quarantine and are still serving good drinks! Thanks Sydney for the latte!

Nice spot, glad there is an alternative to Starbucks, but should really consider changing the coffee lids. Today was about the fifth time I spilled coffee everywhere because the lid would not fully fasten on.
I love it where you can get coffee.
Nice place
Great atmosphere and the baristas are very nice. It is extremely hard to find a spot to seat sometimes so definitely avoid the busy hours and get there early on the weekends.
Love this cafe! Great atmosphere and coffee. The drip coffee is spectacular! The staff is so kind and I love coming here.

Nice atmosphere The baristas are really nice! Great coffee flavor and fair prices! I love the cappuccinos; The only bad thing is that people stay too long on their laptop on the tables and there aren't that many chairs, or space for us customers who only go there to enjoy the coffee can't stay longer, there was a few times that I left.because there was no tables available overall great coffee shop!
Great place in the neighborhood if you’re looking for something a lot better than the deli/dunkin coffee that’s around!
Amazing cold brew and equally amazing staff. Also love how they support local artists!!!

Melbourne style coffee. If you're Australian and crave a good latte. This is the place!
Local vibes, lovely grinds, latte times. Enjoy.

Good coffee, friendly staff, decent wifi. Somehow there is always magically a seat (and often an outlet) available when I'm there. If you arrive hungry, be aware that they tend to run low on pastries in the afternoon. Highly recommend as a spot to work in the neighborhood.

Nice staff/service. Coffee is Irving Farm, so if you're a La Colombe or Stumptown regular you might feel a sense of something missing. Still, the single origin drip does the job in terms of flavor, if you like medium roast black coffee.

Sweet little shop.  Great coffee!
Nice place. Welcoming and courteous staff. Good coffee, better than Starbucks up the street.
Baller service with a smile!!!!

Jon hooked us up with all the info when we bombarded him with questions. We love the cozy space and choice music — esp the vegan friendly options! Third time visiting, love the rotating art and definitely excited to hear about the possibility of open mics at this location soon. 🔥
The staff is really kind. The vegan sándwich is unbelievable.
Nice location. Very delicious coffee, very delicious pastry. Wi-fi available.

Coffee was delicious and fairly priced for artisan coffee. The decor highlights works from local artists, photography and illustrations, with a few cute plants. Open art studio Saturday nights, free WiFi and not too noisy. Will definitely be coming back to support independent coffee in the neighborhood.
Laid-back, unassuming coffee shop in the neighborhood. First time here. Would definitely come back. Reasonable pricing and nice atmosphere.

Barista was really nice and lively, was super helpful and even shows examples of the sizes unlike other places. Tables and restaurant was very clean and nice looking. An absolute gem. There’s no water for in dining, they use ceramic dishes which are VERY nice. Also the free WiFi is an added bonus to get some work here done :)

Coming here the last couple of days has been what I needed. Nice and quiet and peaceful. The staff are friendly, the coffee is really good and the patrons are not too crazy as they are wanting to chit chat or get some business/studying done. This is rapidly becoming my neighborhood café!

Stopped by for the first time today, and loved it here! Cute space, with enough room to hang out for a while. My tea and my friend's hot chocolate were both tasty, and the barista was lovely! All around a great experience.
Great Coffee and delicious pastries!
Kind cashier.

Lovely place, I'm a huge fan of coffee shops and from my experience this is on the more relaxed side. The prices are relatively lower than other coffee shops, but they also have different size cups. The barista was so friendly, the aesthetic feel of the shop is appealing, I love local art, so I was glad to hear that new paintings would be featured on their walls every few weeks. Definitely a must if you live, work or commute near Washington Heights.
Dropped in today for the first time! Really great little spot int he neighborhood, just like back home in Canada.  Great staff and service.  My Americano was delicious! Highly recommend.

Great place, great atmosphere. It would be nice if they opened at 5am but I'm glad they're here and up the block from my home! The prices are reasonable as well and I don't mind paying for a local coffee shop to keep its doors open!

Good coffee, I got a large oat milk latte and it was delicious. They use Irving Farm coffee which is some good stuff imo. Great casual spot. Lots of people working on laptops when we were here Sunday morning, so it looks like a good quiet spot for that.
